19RtpFrameReferenceFinder::ReturnVector RtpVp8RefFinder::ManageFrame(
20 std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject> frame) {
21 FrameDecision decision = ManageFrameInternal(frame.get());
22
23 RtpFrameReferenceFinder::ReturnVector res;
24 switch (decision) {
25 case kStash:
26 if (stashed_frames_.size() > kMaxStashedFrames)
27 stashed_frames_.pop_back();
28 stashed_frames_.push_front(std::move(frame));
29 return res;
30 case kHandOff:
31 res.push_back(std::move(frame));
32 RetryStashedFrames(res);
33 return res;
34 case kDrop:
35 return res;
36 }
37
38 return res;
39}
40
41RtpVp8RefFinder::FrameDecision RtpVp8RefFinder::ManageFrameInternal(
42 RtpFrameObject* frame) {
43 const RTPVideoHeader& video_header = frame->GetRtpVideoHeader();
44 const RTPVideoHeaderVP8& codec_header =
45 absl::get<RTPVideoHeaderVP8>(video_header.video_type_header);
46
47 // Protect against corrupted packets with arbitrary large temporal idx.
48 if (codec_header.temporalIdx >= kMaxTemporalLayers)
49 return kDrop;
50
51 frame->SetSpatialIndex(0);
52 frame->SetId(codec_header.pictureId & 0x7FFF);
53
54 if (last_picture_id_ == -1)
55 last_picture_id_ = frame->Id();
56
57 // Clean up info about not yet received frames that are too old.
58 uint16_t old_picture_id =
59 Subtract<kFrameIdLength>(frame->Id(), kMaxNotYetReceivedFrames);
60 auto clean_frames_to = not_yet_received_frames_.lower_bound(old_picture_id);
61 not_yet_received_frames_.erase(not_yet_received_frames_.begin(),
62 clean_frames_to);
63 // Avoid re-adding picture ids that were just erased.
64 if (AheadOf<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength>(old_picture_id, last_picture_id_)) {
65 last_picture_id_ = old_picture_id;
66 }
67 // Find if there has been a gap in fully received frames and save the picture
68 // id of those frames in |not_yet_received_frames_|.
69 if (AheadOf<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength>(frame->Id(), last_picture_id_)) {
70 do {
71 last_picture_id_ = Add<kFrameIdLength>(last_picture_id_, 1);
72 not_yet_received_frames_.insert(last_picture_id_);
73 } while (last_picture_id_ != frame->Id());
74 }
75
76 int64_t unwrapped_tl0 = tl0_unwrapper_.Unwrap(codec_header.tl0PicIdx & 0xFF);
77
78 // Clean up info for base layers that are too old.
79 int64_t old_tl0_pic_idx = unwrapped_tl0 - kMaxLayerInfo;
80 auto clean_layer_info_to = layer_info_.lower_bound(old_tl0_pic_idx);
81 layer_info_.erase(layer_info_.begin(), clean_layer_info_to);
82
83 if (frame->frame_type() == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
84 if (codec_header.temporalIdx != 0) {
85 return kDrop;
86 }
87 frame->num_references = 0;
88 layer_info_[unwrapped_tl0].fill(-1);
89 UpdateLayerInfoVp8(frame, unwrapped_tl0, codec_header.temporalIdx);
90 return kHandOff;
91 }
92
93 auto layer_info_it = layer_info_.find(
94 codec_header.temporalIdx == 0 ? unwrapped_tl0 - 1 : unwrapped_tl0);
95
96 // If we don't have the base layer frame yet, stash this frame.
97 if (layer_info_it == layer_info_.end())
98 return kStash;
99
100 // A non keyframe base layer frame has been received, copy the layer info
101 // from the previous base layer frame and set a reference to the previous
102 // base layer frame.
103 if (codec_header.temporalIdx == 0) {
104 layer_info_it =
105 layer_info_.emplace(unwrapped_tl0, layer_info_it->second).first;
106 frame->num_references = 1;
107 int64_t last_pid_on_layer = layer_info_it->second[0];
108
109 // Is this an old frame that has already been used to update the state? If
110 // so, drop it.
111 if (AheadOrAt<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength>(last_pid_on_layer, frame->Id())) {
112 return kDrop;
113 }
114
115 frame->references[0] = last_pid_on_layer;
116 UpdateLayerInfoVp8(frame, unwrapped_tl0, codec_header.temporalIdx);
117 return kHandOff;
118 }
119
120 // Layer sync frame, this frame only references its base layer frame.
121 if (codec_header.layerSync) {
122 frame->num_references = 1;
123 int64_t last_pid_on_layer = layer_info_it->second[codec_header.temporalIdx];
124
125 // Is this an old frame that has already been used to update the state? If
126 // so, drop it.
127 if (last_pid_on_layer != -1 &&
128 AheadOrAt<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength>(last_pid_on_layer, frame->Id())) {
129 return kDrop;
130 }
131
132 frame->references[0] = layer_info_it->second[0];
133 UpdateLayerInfoVp8(frame, unwrapped_tl0, codec_header.temporalIdx);
134 return kHandOff;
135 }
136
137 // Find all references for this frame.
138 frame->num_references = 0;
139 for (uint8_t layer = 0; layer <= codec_header.temporalIdx; ++layer) {
140 // If we have not yet received a previous frame on this temporal layer,
141 // stash this frame.
142 if (layer_info_it->second[layer] == -1)
143 return kStash;
144
145 // If the last frame on this layer is ahead of this frame it means that
146 // a layer sync frame has been received after this frame for the same
147 // base layer frame, drop this frame.
148 if (AheadOf<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength>(layer_info_it->second[layer],
149 frame->Id())) {
150 return kDrop;
151 }
152
153 // If we have not yet received a frame between this frame and the referenced
154 // frame then we have to wait for that frame to be completed first.
155 auto not_received_frame_it =
156 not_yet_received_frames_.upper_bound(layer_info_it->second[layer]);
157 if (not_received_frame_it != not_yet_received_frames_.end() &&
158 AheadOf<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength>(frame->Id(),
159 *not_received_frame_it)) {
160 return kStash;
161 }
162
163 if (!(AheadOf<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength>(frame->Id(),
164 layer_info_it->second[layer]))) {
165 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Frame with picture id " << frame->Id()
166 << " and packet range [" << frame->first_seq_num()
167 << ", " << frame->last_seq_num()
168 << "] already received, "
169 " dropping frame.";
170 return kDrop;
171 }
172
173 ++frame->num_references;
174 frame->references[layer] = layer_info_it->second[layer];
175 }
176
177 UpdateLayerInfoVp8(frame, unwrapped_tl0, codec_header.temporalIdx);
178 return kHandOff;
179}
180
181void RtpVp8RefFinder::UpdateLayerInfoVp8(RtpFrameObject* frame,
182 int64_t unwrapped_tl0,
183 uint8_t temporal_idx) {
184 auto layer_info_it = layer_info_.find(unwrapped_tl0);
185
186 // Update this layer info and newer.
187 while (layer_info_it != layer_info_.end()) {
188 if (layer_info_it->second[temporal_idx] != -1 &&
189 AheadOf<uint16_t, kFrameIdLength>(layer_info_it->second[temporal_idx],
190 frame->Id())) {
191 // The frame was not newer, then no subsequent layer info have to be
192 // update.
193 break;
194 }
195
196 layer_info_it->second[temporal_idx] = frame->Id();
197 ++unwrapped_tl0;
198 layer_info_it = layer_info_.find(unwrapped_tl0);
199 }
200 not_yet_received_frames_.erase(frame->Id());
201
202 UnwrapPictureIds(frame);
203}
204
205void RtpVp8RefFinder::RetryStashedFrames(
206 RtpFrameReferenceFinder::ReturnVector& res) {
207 bool complete_frame = false;
208 do {
209 complete_frame = false;
210 for (auto frame_it = stashed_frames_.begin();
211 frame_it != stashed_frames_.end();) {
212 FrameDecision decision = ManageFrameInternal(frame_it->get());
213
214 switch (decision) {
215 case kStash:
216 ++frame_it;
217 break;
218 case kHandOff:
219 complete_frame = true;
220 res.push_back(std::move(*frame_it));
221 ABSL_FALLTHROUGH_INTENDED;
222 case kDrop:
223 frame_it = stashed_frames_.erase(frame_it);
224 }
225 }
226 } while (complete_frame);
227}
228
229void RtpVp8RefFinder::UnwrapPictureIds(RtpFrameObject* frame) {
230 for (size_t i = 0; i < frame->num_references; ++i)
231 frame->references[i] = unwrapper_.Unwrap(frame->references[i]);
232 frame->SetId(unwrapper_.Unwrap(frame->Id()));
233}
234
235void RtpVp8RefFinder::ClearTo(uint16_t seq_num) {
236 auto it = stashed_frames_.begin();
237 while (it != stashed_frames_.end()) {
238 if (AheadOf<uint16_t>(seq_num, (*it)->first_seq_num())) {
239 it = stashed_frames_.erase(it);
240 } else {
241 ++it;
242 }
243 }
244}
